KEY_SALT is the cache namespace version: it must be bumped whenever the SCHEMA_SQL table shape, payload schema, or any hashed key input changes, so old rows stop matching and a gc pass removes them. Editing a table definition without bumping KEY_SALT silently serves rows written under an incompatible shape; nothing mechanical enforces the bump.
